Background
 The Army Contracting Command at Aberdeen Proving Ground, Maryland, and Product Lead Attack (PL EA) are conducting market research to identify qualified parties interested in becoming the prime contractor for the Modi system. 

The Modi FamilFoS is a modular mounted and dismounted defensive Electronic Attack (EA) system designed to provide operationally deployed Soldiers with the capability to maneuver effectively in the electromagnetic spectrum (EMS). This system supports Electronic Counter Measures (ECM) warfare and generates electronic attack fires to deny enemy freedom of action in the EMS, operating worldwide to support U.S. forces' battlefield dominance.

Work Details
 The anticipated requirements for sustainment and procurement services for the Modi system include: 
1. Provide Sustainment support; 
2. Ability to procure spare parts; 
3. Mechanism to explore extended capability of the Modi; 
4. Support for both Dismounted and Mounted Modi portfolio; 
5. Material and Software Maintenance Services; 
6. Field Service Support; 
7. Training Support Services; 
8. Safety; 
9. Operators Manual; 
10. Program Management; 
11. Security; 
12. Contractor Manpower Reporting; 
13. Field testing.

Place of Performance
 The contract will be performed at various locations worldwide as it supports U.S. forces.
